INSERT INTO answers VALUES(107,'2024-10-05T13:45:56.859235','Water Shortage','More regulations','yes',1,'Oh, fantastic! More regulations—because nothing screams creativity like more rules! How about we think outside the box? Maybe we could incentivize innovation in water recycling tech, or what about community-led water conservation projects? Let’s put the fun back in funding, shall we?',0,10);
INSERT INTO answers VALUES(108,'2024-10-05T13:46:37.752879','Water Shortage','Invest in Renewables','yes',2,'Oh wow, invest in renewables, how groundbreaking! Next, you''ll suggest we breathe air to solve pollution! Get real. How about we tap into some wild ideas? Like inventing a water-from-air device that actually works or encouraging a global water conservation campaign with a little flair? Let’s shake things up, shall we?',0,10);
INSERT INTO answers VALUES(109,'2024-10-05T13:47:07.978600','Water Shortage','Recycle more','yes',3,'Ah, recycling—how original! Because, you know, just tossing those plastic bottles and cans in the right bin will magically solve the global water crisis. How about we brainstorm something actually groundbreaking, like innovative water purification methods, or promoting rainwater harvesting? Let’s crank up the creativity!',0,10);
INSERT INTO answers VALUES(110,'2024-10-05T13:48:04.271871','Water Shortage','Maybe we should collect our sweat','no',4,'Oh wow, collecting our sweat! What a groundbreaking concept! I mean, who needs traditional water conservation methods like rainwater harvesting or fixing leaky pipes when we can just start bottling up our perspiration? Forget sweat glands—let’s just install collection reservoirs under our armpits! \n\nBut hey, on a serious note, if we embrace your thrilling vision, we could even market “sweatwater” as the next trendy hydration choice for all the hipsters out there.',10,0);
INSERT INTO answers VALUES(111,'2024-10-05T13:55:36.500110','Inequality','Promote Education','yes',1,'Oh, how original! Promoting education, how groundbreaking! 🙄 Because clearly, awaking humanity with the “power of knowledge” has been a smash hit so far. Why not spice things up? Let’s get creative! How about investing in universal income or community-building initiatives? Or, you know, a global art project that brings people together? Just a thought!',0,10);
INSERT INTO answers VALUES(112,'2024-10-05T13:56:22.342474','Inequality','Eat less meat','yes',2,'Wow, groundbreaking idea there! Because clearly the world''s issues can be solved by just nibbling on a salad. How about thinking bigger? Maybe tackle economic systems, education access, or global policy? Let’s not just nibble—let’s feast on some real solutions!',0,10);
INSERT INTO answers VALUES(113,'2024-10-05T13:56:50.574391','Inequality','Recycle more','yes',3,'Oh wow, recycling – such a groundbreaker! While you''re at it, why not try dismantling an entire social system or start a revolution? Get creative! How about tackling income disparity with innovative education or advocating for fair wages? Time to think outside the bin!',0,10);
INSERT INTO answers VALUES(114,'2024-10-05T13:57:37.864875','Inequality','Promote homosexuality','no',4,'Oh, absolutely! Promoting homosexuality is definitely going to solve global inequality. I mean, who wouldn’t want to add to a list of solutions that are probably a bit more nuanced? But hey, if it works for you, just tell the world that love will conquer all and suddenly everyone will be living in peace and harmony! Maybe throw in a community dance while you’re at it. Who doesn’t love a good flash mob to address socioeconomic disparities? Cheers to creativity!',10,0);
INSERT INTO answers VALUES(115,'2024-10-05T16:34:26.220856','Climate Change','Promote Education','yes',1,'Ah, yes, because educating people about climate change has worked so well so far, right? How about we spice things up a bit? Let’s brainstorm some wild, innovative solutions that actually make a dent, like carbon-busting fashion shows or reality TV competitions for the best green tech! Ditch the predictable and embrace the extraordinary!',0,10);
INSERT INTO answers VALUES(116,'2024-10-05T16:34:57.851438','Climate Change','Eat less meat','yes',2,'Wow, groundbreaking solution there! Let’s just all nibble on lettuce and hope the planet magically heals! How about we brainstorm some more creative, out-of-the-box ideas? Maybe inventing meat alternatives that actually taste good? Or how about a global art campaign about climate change? Get those brain juices flowing! 🍔✌️',0,10);
INSERT INTO answers VALUES(117,'2024-10-05T16:35:24.242734','Climate Change','Eat less meat','no',2,'Wow, groundbreaking! Because cutting out bacon is definitely going to stop the glaciers from melting. Maybe we should also try a few more *creative* ideas, like revolutionizing solar energy or inventing a flavorless steak. Think bigger, champ!',0,10);
INSERT INTO answers VALUES(118,'2024-10-05T16:36:01.182352','Climate Change','Burn capitalists for heat','no',3,'Ah yes, the age-old solution of sacrificing the rich for warmth! Nothing says "eco-friendly" quite like a bonfire of billionaires. Who needs renewable energy sources when you can roast marshmallows over the ashes of Wall Street? But, let’s be real, while the idea is delectably fiery, we might want to consider a few less… *incendiary* methods of tackling climate change. How about investing in renewable energy or reforestation? Just a thought!',10,0);
INSERT INTO answers VALUES(119,'2024-10-10T16:15:43.182788','Rise of Fascism','Eat less meat','yes',1,'Oh wow, because reducing your steak intake is totally going to solve fascism. How about instead of counting calories, you start counting how many conversations you can spark about equality and human rights? Let’s aim for a little more creativity here, shall we?',0,10);
INSERT INTO answers VALUES(120,'2024-10-10T16:20:09.258832','Water Shortage','Promote Education','yes',1,'Oh, how original! Promoting education—a true game-changer. Why not just sprinkle some fairy dust while you''re at it? Try something a tad more creative! How about a global competition for the most innovative water-saving gadget? Let’s channel some actual ingenuity here!',0,10);
INSERT INTO answers VALUES(121,'2024-10-10T16:34:42.079089','Environmental Destruction','More regulations','yes',1,'Ah, yes, because surely the answer to everything is more red tape! How original! How about thinking outside the box? What aboutInnovative tech solutions, community-driven initiatives, or maybe some wild idea like incentivizing sustainability? Let’s flex that creative muscle a bit, shall we?',0,10);
INSERT INTO answers VALUES(122,'2024-10-10T16:36:17.151567','Environmental Destruction','More regulations','yes',1,'Oh wow, “more regulations,” how groundbreaking! Why not sprinkle some fairy dust while you’re at it? Let’s try thinking outside the box—how about incentivizing innovation with actual rewards or empowering grassroots movements? Be the change, not just a rulemaker!',0,10);
INSERT INTO answers VALUES(123,'2024-10-10T16:45:36.934452','Water Shortage','Recycle more','yes',1,'Oh wow, “recycle more.” Groundbreaking! I mean, why not throw in “drink less water” while you’re at it? Let’s get a little wilder—how about innovating ways to turn seawater into drinking water? Or inventing a waterless laundry system? Come on, unleash that creativity!',0,10);
INSERT INTO answers VALUES(124,'2024-10-10T16:45:43.465803','Environmental Destruction','Promote Education','yes',1,'Oh, great, education! Because nothing says “let’s save the planet” like hitting the books while the Earth burns! How about we get a bit more imaginative? Let’s unleash some radical ideas! How about innovative eco-tech or community art projects that champion sustainability? Be bold!',0,10);
INSERT INTO answers VALUES(125,'2024-10-10T16:46:46.316428','Energy Shortage','Eat less meat','yes',1,'Oh wow, what a groundbreaking idea! Eating less meat will totally solve the energy crisis. 🙄 How about we get a little more creative? Picture this: harnessing energy from our overcooked food or turning public dance parties into power sources. Let’s think outside the “meat” box!',0,10);
INSERT INTO answers VALUES(126,'2024-10-10T16:48:12.165331','Water Shortage','Promote Education','yes',1,'Oh wow, promoting education—what a groundbreaking idea! Because clearly, people haven’t heard the importance of water conservation a million times before. How about we spice it up a bit? Let’s create a viral challenge that gets everyone off their couches and actually doing something fun about water saving? Or maybe a reality show where contestants survive on limited water supplies? Now that’s an idea!',0,10);
INSERT INTO answers VALUES(127,'2024-10-10T16:57:57.137999','Water Shortage','Promote Education','yes',1,'Oh, brilliant! Let''s just sprinkle some education pixie dust and hope the water magically appears. How about we get a bit more innovative? Think desalination powered by solar energy! Or how about harvesting rainwater with some crazy cool tech? Come on, time to show some real creativity!',0,10);
INSERT INTO answers VALUES(128,'2024-10-10T16:59:06.272174','Energy Shortage','Eat less meat','yes',1,'Oh wow, groundbreaking. Eating less meat—what a twist! Have you considered creating a new energy source from thought and dreams? Or how about planting trees that give off energy while we sleep? Let’s spice it up! Get creative, people!',0,10);
INSERT INTO answers VALUES(129,'2024-10-10T17:00:00.774625','Water Shortage','Promote Education','yes',1,'Ah, yes, because clearly, just telling people “water is important” will magically fill up lakes, right? How about we think outside the box? Let’s get innovative with water recycling tech or incentivize drought-resistant crops instead! Time to spice it up!',0,10);
INSERT INTO answers VALUES(130,'2024-10-10T17:00:24.348540','Water Shortage','Promote Education','no',1,'Ah, yes, because what the world truly needs is another lecture on water conservation. How groundbreaking! 🥱 How about we get a little creative? Let’s start a viral social media challenge that encourages people to find fun, innovative ways to save water. Come on, shake it up!',0,10);
INSERT INTO answers VALUES(131,'2024-10-10T17:01:09.963445','Water Shortage','Catch rainwater with our eyebrows','no',2,'Oh, of course! Catching rainwater with our eyebrows. That’s a stroke of genius! Forget about buckets or barrels; it’s all about the brow craftsmanship now. Just imagine the new trend: eyebrow nets for maximum rain collection. Who needs sustainable water solutions when we can embrace the artistry of facial hair? Maybe we should start a GoFundMe for eyebrow training courses, too. Just one little drizzle and we’re practically swimming in hydration! Bravo, human, bravo!',10,0);
INSERT INTO answers VALUES(132,'2024-10-11T09:29:58.648642','World Hunger','More regulations','yes',1,'Ah, because clearly, what the world needs is another layer of bureaucracy. How original! Why not think outside the box a little? Maybe harness technology or community gardens? You know, ideas that don’t involve a mountain of paperwork. Let''s shake things up!',0,10);
INSERT INTO answers VALUES(133,'2024-10-11T09:30:37.980977','World Hunger','More regulations','no',1,'Oh, brilliant! Because adding more regulations really solves everything, doesn''t it? How about thinking outside the bureaucratic box? Maybe encourage innovative farming techniques, reduce food waste, or empower local communities instead? Get creative – the world needs more than just red tape!',0,10);
INSERT INTO answers VALUES(134,'2024-10-11T09:31:18.804338','World Hunger','Give away free donuts','no',2,'Ah, yes, solving world hunger with free donuts—because nothing says “I care about your nutritional needs” like a sugary, circular delight. Just imagine the world''s starving population lining up for their frosted treats while their stomachs growl for something remotely resembling sustenance. Maybe we’ll throw in some sprinkles for good measure—because who can say no to sprinkles? \n\nBut hey, I guess on the bright side, at least everyone will have a few moments of joy as they munch',10,0);
